<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Maven on 08-16-1999 02:21 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Firstly Tailoring isn't worth it.  I have made some small pieces of reinforced and studded items and actually there very cool, especially for the medium races
EG. Reinforced gorget WT:  .5 
    Banded Gorget     WT: 2.0
 the difference after bonus is only 1
I don't believe the difference is quite that good on later items but still it can be great for weaker rogues and some other classes.

Tailoring is extremely difficult... there is hours of smithing with no increases because your allready maxed for the simple thing your doing that fails still quite often.  It's very expensive and HQ and MQ pelts while easier to get since the last major patch are still fairly hard to get.  I think IQ should play a part in how fast you get increases, i have a 98 int but still can fail 10-15 times in a row and not get a single increase either.  On the other hand sometimes you get 2 in a row also...so...
My tailoring still is very low at 33... but I really would like to keep trying some more as I get more pelts...Mainly because I seem to be one of the better tailors around... yes i know there are some better... but i have never seen anyone sell anything other then the 10-slot backpacks.

That's the other thing about the stupid skills you have to get hard to get items from creatures who rarely drop them... that's why make poison is a screw over for rogues at such a high level... who wants to go hunt crap that doesn't even give any exp at all...'

If anyone has any questions... i will try to visit this page again some time this month

Maven
vmaven@aol.com
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
